        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 8:06PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 806 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Monroe, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Mercer
County.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
